==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neishout
<hw>Neis"hout</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From D.
<ets>niezen</ets> to sneeze + <ets>hout</ets> wood.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The mahogany-like wood of the South African tree
<spn>Pteroxylon utile</spn>, the sawdust of which causes violent
sneezing (whence the name). Also called
<altname>sneezewood</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neither</ent>⟦br⟧
